1. c4 e5
{ The most principled reply. Black occupies the centre with a pawn, as White 'failed' to do the same thing on move 1. We will fianchetto our bishop almost all of the time in this proposed repertoire. The bishop helps to control d5 and the long diagonal. White's play will usually be focused on the queenside. Moves like b4 or prep moves for this kind of play are commonplace. With his next moves Black choosed the line. We have 5 Chapters total to provide details of the play. }
*

