[White "1 c4 e5 2 g3 Nc6 3 Bg2 Others"]
[Black "1 c4 e5 2 g3 Nc6 3 Bg2 Others 12"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 e5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 f5
{ The Reversed Grand Prix Attack. Other options in this position are mostly just transpositional. }
4. Nc3 Nf6 5. e3 d5 { The brutal solution, but there are some alternatives. }
6. Nxd5 Nxd5 7. cxd5 Nb4 8. d3
{ Returning the pawn will lead to a small edge. } 8... Nxd5 9. Nf3 Bd6 10. O-O
Nf6 11. Qb3 Qe7 12. e4
{ White has slightly better chances is this position. . ..f5 has weakened the Black kingside and he still has to spend time to get castled. }
*

