1. c4 e5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 f5
{ The Reversed Grand Prix Attack. Other options in this position are mostly just transpositional. }
4. Nc3 Nf6 5. e3 Bb4
{ White is ready now for Nge2, so Bb4 is nothing much to worry about. } 6. Nge2
O-O 7. O-O Bxc3
{ not a happy move, but the alternative doesn't convince either. } 8. Nxc3 d6
9. d4 e4 10. f3 exf3 11. Qxf3 Bd7 12. b3 Rb8 13. Bb2 Qe8 14. Rae1
{ This was the game Granda Zuniga,J  (2663)  -Caruana,F  (2801)  Tromso 2014. Quite a surprise to see Caruana play into this position. He got away with a draw out of this unattractive setup. }
*

