1. c4 e5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 d6 { is a related idea. } 4. Nc3 Be6 5. d3 Qd7 6. Rb1
{ Just like in the main line. White also has other setups of course, like 6 e4 for example. }
6... g6 7. b4 Bg7 8. b5 Nd8 9. Nd5
{ This Knight is quite annoying for Black, therefore he usually kicks it with ... c6, which gives us the open b-file. }
9... c6 10. bxc6 bxc6 11. Nc3 f5 12. Qa4
{ White has good prospects on the queenside. } *

[Event "?"]
