{ The Reversed Closed Sicilian. This is a quite solid option for Black against the English Opening. However it is well established that Black has no problems whatsoever in the Closed Sicilian after 1 e4 c5 2 Nc3 and an extra tempo is quite helpful for the queenside play, leading to a comfortable situation for White. }
