5. a3 { Now } 5... Nh6
{ Black emphasizes control over d4, but it does not have that much to do on f5 with a pawn on e3. Let's have a look at a sample line. }
6. Rb1 a5 7. e3 Nf5 8. Nge2 d6 9. O-O O-O 10. b3 e5 11. Bb2 Be6
{ White has good control here over d5 and b5. Possible plans may involve a long term d2-d4 anyway or even f2-f4. Note that Black has no pawn breaks with is very comfortable for White to improve his position. }
12. Rc1 *

