[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "1 c4 c5 2 g3 Nf6 3 Bg2 d5"]
[Black "1 c4 c5 2 g3 Nf6 3 Bg2 d5 4"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 c5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 d5
{ Black opens up the centre. This is a very ambitious and interesting line. }
4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Nc3 Nc7
{ Clearly the best option. Black keeps the Knight and intends to increase his central presence with ...e5 for a reversed Maroczy bind. }
6. Nf3
{ This is my main recommendation, but I like to point out an interesting alternative in Qa4+. }
6... Nc6 7. a3
{ This is logical alternative. White has not castled yet, so let's use this fact. }
7... g6 8. h4 h5 { is more solid, but I still like White after something like }
9. d3 Bg7 10. Be3 b6 11. Ng5
{ Note that the ensertion of h4/h5 gave White this nice outpost as playing ...f6 is much harder now for Black due to the g6 pawn/square. }
*

