1. c4 c5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 d5
{ Black opens up the centre. This is a very ambitious and interesting line. }
4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Nc3 Nc7 { +=4 } 6. Qa4+ Bd7
{ This is the pawn sac. Other moves are just better for White. } 7. Qb3 Nc6 8.
Qxb7 Nd4 { The only move to pose problems. } 9. Qe4 g6 10. Qb1 Bg7 11. e3 Nc6
12. Nge2
{ This is the critical position of this Qa4+ line. White is better if Black does not know/find this. The position is certainly not to everybody's taste. I think that White is a bit better here as I doubt that Black has full compensation. However I understand if you dislike to defend a bit with White for a pawn. Therefore I explored the lines that are now my main recommendation. These should suit almost everybody. Still Qa4+ is a tricky alternative ! }
*

