1. c4 c5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 d5
{ Black opens up the centre. This is a very ambitious and interesting line. }
4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Nc3 Nc7 { +=4 } 6. Qa4+ Qd7
{ This is a very concrete approach. The somewhat surprising fact is that Black is almost forced to sac a pawn now. Let's have a look. }
7. Qxd7+ Nxd7 8. Nf3 e5 9. d3 Be7 10. Nd2 Rb8 11. Nc4 Ne6 12. Bd2
{ White has some other option along the way, but in general Black has a coordination issue here. White is for choice. }
