1. c4 c6 2. g3
{ almost mandatory, as we need to address the 1 c4 Nf6 2 g3 c6 move order as well. However in this concrete position there are many alternatives. }
2... d5 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Bg2
{ This is the Reti Gambit. There are some theoriticians who believe that White never can be better, because d5/c6 is limiting the Bishop. I never understood that reasoning to be honest. If this is so important, why isn't the Closed Catalan great for Black ? Anyway, the coming lines are quite concrete. Let's check the overview. }
4... dxc4 { The most critical move. } 5. O-O
{ The best move after Black took the pawn. It leads to sharp and very complicated play which is discussed in Chapter 15. }
