1. c4 c6 2. g3 d5 3. Nf3 Nf6
{ This is the most popular move, only later deciding what to go for. Black however may also commit right away. Quite often it just comes to the same thing, as Nf6 is a rather natural move. }
4. Bg2 Bg4
{ This natural move is fine, but Black has to know what he is doing. Some continuations that look perfectly normal lead to severe Problems. }
5. Ne5 Bh5
{ This basically will come to the same thing as Bf5, there is just a little difference. }
6. cxd5 Nxd5
{ This is possible now, as there is no fork compared to Bf5 earlier, but White is just more comfortable. He enjoys the better centre with c-pawn traded aginst d pawn without any concessions. }
7. Nc3 e6 8. O-O Nd7 9. Nf3
{ Retreating is best here, keeping pieces on with Black having less space. } *

