[White "1 c4 c6 2 g3 d5 3 Nf3 - g6 setups"]
[Black "1 c4 c6 2 g3 d5 3 Nf3 - g6 setups 7"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 c6 2. g3 d5 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Bg2 g6 5. b3
{ I like this double fianchetto, but White has other ideas as well. } 5... Bg7
6. Bb2 Qb6
{ This is a quite tricky move ! Black has Ng4 and dxc4 in store. The coming line is useful to know. }
7. Qc2 Bf5 8. d3 dxc4 9. Qxc4 Ng4
{ This fails, but is scary if you never have seen the line before. } 10. Bxg7
Qxf2+ 11. Kd2 Qe3+ 12. Kc3 { Only move. } 12... Rg8 13. Bd4 Qxe2 14. Nbd2 Qxg2
15. Rae1 { White is winning, due to the threat 16 Rhg1 Qh3 17 Ng5. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
