1. c4 c6 2. g3 d5 3. Nf3
{ This one is going to be the most complicated chapter of the whole repertoire. Many lines of the presented repertoire can be played based on 'feel' and general strategic understanding, but not this one ! Please make sure to study the upcoming lines and add your own ideas or that of your computer.It will pay off ! }
3... Nf6 4. Bg2 dxc4 5. O-O
{ White has tried some other moves here  (5 Qc2, 5 Na3)  , but nowadays it seems clear that 5 O-O is the way to go. Now Black has some options at his disposal and unfortunately none of them is easily dispatched, they are all complicated. }
