Nxd5
{ The classical approach. There are some other lines, but this is rather simple to learn and should preserve a small edge. }
8... exd5 9. d4 O-O 10. dxc5 Bxc5 11. Bg5 f6
{ This is not a move that Black loves to play. It weakens many squares in the centre and around the king. }
12. Bd2 Be6 13. e3 Qd7 14. Bc3 Rad8 15. Bd4 Nxd4 16. Nxd4
{ With a very comfortable situation for White. He has good control and clear targets to play against. }
