{ This is a very solid option for Black. } 6. Qxc4 c5 7. Ne5 Qc8 8. O-O Nc6 9.
Nxd7 Qxd7
{ This is Black's idea. He gives up the Bishop pair, but retains god central control. }
10. Nc3 Be7 11. Qa4 Rc8 12. d3 O-O 13. Be3 Rfd8 14. Rac1
{ This was the game Nakamura,H  (2814)  -Eljanov,P  (2717)  Baku 2015. I still call this slightly better for White due to the Bishops - but they are not easy to use here because Black is very well coordinated. Patience is key here. }
