1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 { The most frequently played move is the natural }
3... Nf6 { , but Black has some alternatives. } 4. Nf3 dxc4
{ The most critical move here. } 5. Qa4+
{ no fancy stuff - let's get the pawn back. } 5... c6 6. Qxc4 b5 7. Qb3
{ This seems to be the best square, getting away from the c-file. } 7... Bb7 8.
O-O Nbd7 9. d4
{ A very logical sequence. Now Black either tries to speed up ...c5 by going ...a6 or plays Be7 to get nearer to castling. Good news for White: Ne5 is going to be the reponse and the play is quite similar. }
9... Be7 10. Ne5 Qb6 11. Be3 Qc7 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13. Nd2
{ Is a typical line that is good for White. Black has a hard time getting in ...c5. }
