1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 { The most frequently played move is the natural }
3... Nf6 { , but Black has some alternatives. } 4. Nf3 dxc4
{ The most critical move here. } 5. Qa4+
{ no fancy stuff - let's get the pawn back. } 5... Nbd7
{ This is the most popular move, but the alternatives are very viable and need to be checked carefully. }
6. Qxc4 a6 7. Qb3
{ Important prophylaxis. The Q has to move anyway, so better do it rightaway to avoid getting hit with a tempo. }
7... c5 8. a4
{ White wants to get the a-pawn up to a5 to have a bind on the queenside. }
8... Bd6 9. d3 Rb8 10. a5 Bc7 11. Bd2 O-O 12. O-O Nd5 13. Nc3
{ this is the mentioned bind structure. Black is restricted and } 13... b5 14.
axb6 Rxb6 15. Qa3 { gives White an excellent structural advantage. } *

