4. Qa4+ { Let's get the pawn back by simple means. } 4... Nd7 5. Qxc4 c5 6. Nf3
{ now most of the time Black just plays Nf6 to transpose to the main line, but sometimes he tried to benefit from omitting the move. }
6... b6 7. Nd4 { initiates a forced sequence that is good for White. } 7... Ne5
8. Nc6 Nxc4 9. Nxd8 Rb8 10. Nc6 Bb7 11. O-O Ra8
{ All forced up to this point. } 12. d3 Nd6 13. d4
{ and the game opens up favorably for White. } 13... cxd4 14. Nxd4 Bxg2 15.
Kxg2
{ And White has a very nagging edge here. He is quicker on the crucial open files, The N on d6 is misplaced and c6 is weak. }
