1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2
{ The most frequently played move is the natural  The most important one probably is }
3... dxc4 { , which is quite similar to dxc4 as discussed in the main line. }
4. Qa4+ { Let's get the pawn back by simple means. } 4... c6 5. Qxc4 b5 6. Qb3
{ This is the best square. The Queen leaves the c-file. } 6... Bb7 7. Nf3 Nd7
{ If Black goes Nf6 here we would transpose to dxc4. } 8. d4 a6 9. Ne5
{ Immediately using the diagonal. } 9... Ne7 10. O-O Nf5 11. Rd1 Nxe5 12. dxe5
Qb6 { An interesting position with some options for White. } 13. Be3 Nxe3 14.
Qxe3 Qxe3 15. fxe3 Be7 16. Nc3
{ White has enough play for his terrible structure. I think it is about equal, but still play left. }
