[Result "*"]

1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nf3 Be7
{ The most classical setup, usually signaling that Black is aiming to defend the Catalan main line. }
5. O-O O-O { +=4 } 6. d4
{ This leads to the main line Catalan. This opening enjoys an excellent reputation for combining solidity with chances to play for a win. It is however outside of the focus of this repertoire, as we try to stay within English/Reti territory. Objectively speaking this transposition is probably the most testing for Black, so a way to go is to learn the lines presented here and maybe the Catalan at a later stage if you feel the need or are just interested in broadening your knowledge. }
