{ This looks rather slow for White, but it has some points that took me a while to understand. Black can't easily play ...d5 or any other pawn advance. In the meantime White goes for f4 to increase central pressure. I guess it is an equal position, but certainly not a boring one. }
11... d5 12. exd5 cxd5 13. Bg5 *

