1. c4 Nf6
{ This is actually Black's most popular move ! However it very often transposes to other systems once Black plays a pawn in the centre. }
2. g3 { As explained in the intro this is consistent with our repertoire. }
2... g6
{ In this chapter we deal with the King's Indian setup mostly. There are tons of transpositions here. }
3. Bg2 Bg7
{ By far the most common move, but here and on the next couple of moves Black always has the option of playing ...c6. }
4. Nc3 O-O 5. d3 { The 'English' move. } 5... d6 6. Rb1
{ Consistent with our repertoire. } 6... c6
{ This makes a lot of sense, as White cannot answer routinely here. } 7. e4
{ Again the reply to ...c6. } 7... e5 8. Nge2
