1. c4 Nf6 2. g3 d5 3. cxd5 Nxd5 4. Bg2 g6 { Going Grnfeld style. } 5. Nc3 Nxc3
{ This is just as popular as ...Nb6, but I think White has an easier job here than after the retreat. White's structure with the extra centre pawn is better and with White not being committed in the centre yet it is more difficult for Black to get play compared to the proper Grnfeld. }
6. bxc3 Bg7 { +=4 } 7. Rb1 Nc6 { The quieter alternative. } 8. Nf3 O-O 9. O-O
b6 10. Qc2 { White will occupy the centre with pawns eventually. } *

