4... Nf6 5. d3 d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. e5 Nfd7 8. d4 c5 9. f4 Nc6 10. Be3
{ This position is quite unusual for our repertoire. The good news is: White is just better ! }
10... cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Bxd4 Bc5 { +=4 } 13. Bb5 O-O 14. Bxd7 Qxd7
{ This is something to avoid. } 15. O-O Rac8 16. Rf2 Bxd4 17. Qxd4 Rc4
{ And Black was fine in Siebrecht,S  (2463)  -Khenkin,I  (2632)  Osterburg 2012 }
*

