{ This move was recommended by GM Simon Williams in his book "The Killer Dutch", but I think White is better in more than one way. }
11. e3 a5
{ This is the line given by Williams. It is less powerful than f4, but still good for White. }
12. a3 Nd7 13. Nd3 e5 14. d5 Ne7
{ which he calls unclear. It is just better for White after a normal move like }
15. e4
{ White has more space, better pieces etc. Where is Black's counterplay ? And what was the point of going Ng8-f6-e4-c5-d7 after all... }
